  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Export Sales Coordinator",
  "description": "<p><strong>Export Sales Coordinator</strong></p>\n<p>The incumbent will work alongside with the team manager to support the Export Sales team in the follow up on and support of the sales destined to export markets.</p>\n<p><strong>The Job Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Handle sales enquiries, generate quotations, and coordinate order consolidation</li>\n  <li>Ensure customer’s order is promptly processed and invoiced accurately on a timely basis</li>\n  <li>Prepare and organize shipping documents for export shipping clearance (including Bill of      Lading, packing list, shipping certificate, declaration, certificate of origin, marine insurance)</li>\n  <li>Provide timely updates on the cargoes estimated arrival / departure dates to all stakeholders</li>\n  <li>Liaise and coordinate with Logistics Department on delivery schedule and inventory matters</li>\n  <li>Ensure all invoices from all external service providers (eg. freight forwarders) are promptly submitted to the Accounts department for processing</li>\n  <li>Assist in processing warranty and insurance claims</li>\n  <li>Maintain accurate records of all sales and shipping documents</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>What It Takes:</strong></p>\n<p>· Minimum a Diploma or equivalent</p>\n<p>· Meticulous, detail-oriented, and organized, with sense of initiative and able to work under minimal supervision</p>\n<p>· Possess relevant experience in sales support or sales coordinator</p>\n<p>· Possess good communication and interpersonal skills</p>\n<p>· Proficient in Microsoft Office</p>",
